</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFBE6A01FD2490381D1DB3B2" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFBE6A01FD2490381D1DB3B2" blockId="69.[726,1327,1511,1937]" lastBlockId="69.[120,1328,1945,3478]" pageId="69" pageNumber="827">
Current members of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FBE490381A8DBD4C" box="[1048,1165,1633,1662]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Arielulus</taxonomicName>
were long treated as a species group within Pipustrellus, or sometimes 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FC2D90F51A46BDFF" box="[977,1094,1708,1741]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eptesicus</taxonomicName>
, on the grounds of karyology and bacular morphology. In 1987, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FCD390A21DA4BC2E" box="[815,932,1787,1820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Arielulus</taxonomicName>
was established as a subgenus within Pipustrellus. In 1999, G. Csorba and Lee Lingling concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FB4691131B2FBC59" box="[1210,1327,1866,1899]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Arielulus</taxonomicName>
was distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FC1D912D1A6DBCA3" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[993,1133,1908,1937]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
, raising it to generic rank, with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FE7191C01C25BC88" authorityName="Kock &amp; Storch" authorityYear="1996" box="[397,549,1945,1978]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Thainycteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Thainycteris</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym; these two were later split. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FB2491C01F19BCD3" baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="societatis">Arielulus societatis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FE9E91991FF8BCD3" authorityName="Francis &amp; Hill" authorityYear="1984" box="[354,504,1984,2017]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cuprosus">A. cuprosus</taxonomicName>
were at times regarded as merely lowland forms of A. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FAF591991EF7B33B" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="circumdatus">circumdatus</taxonomicName>
. Chinese populations have sometimes been separated as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBE6A01FBDB91B11AEDB33B" box="[1063,1261,2024,2057]" pageId="69" pageNumber="827" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="drungicus">race drungicus</taxonomicName>
, but they differ only in minor dental characters; Vietnamese (Dalat Plateau) specimens are slightly smaller with less red than those from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFBE6A01FD0F9E6E1D48B36A" box="[755,840,2103,2136]" name="Nepal" pageId="69" pageNumber="827">Nepal</collectingCountry>
; more research is needed to assess the degree of intraspecific variation. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
